Short CommunicationFirst detection of blood in the gut of wild caught male sandflies in southern BrazilDuring a study on the dynamics of the transmission of cutaneous and mucocutaneous leishmaniasis in Rio Grande do Sul, southern Brazil, male phlebotomine sandflies (Diptera: Psychodidae, Phlebotominae) were found with blood in the alimentary canal although it is common belief that only females take bloodmeals.